casebody.data:
Sayre, Appellee, v. Hoelzle-Sayre, Appellant.

[Cite as Sayre v. Hoelzle-Sayre (1995), 72 Ohio St.3d 1218.]

(No. 94-1094 Submitted June 6, 1995 Decided July 19, 1995.) B. Mark Davis, for appellee. Britz & Zemmelman and Harland M. Britz, for appellant.

The appeal is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Wright, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer and Cook, JJ., concur. Resnick, J., dissents, and would reverse the judgment of the court of appeals and remand for a new hearing.
